Friends have indicated that she wants financial compensation from the President, who fears that she will turn into a loose cannon who could damage him.

Mr Cameron is hosting the summit at RAF Brize Norton, the air force base in his Oxfordshire constituency.

Energy and defence policy are expected to dominate talks on Friday morning, with senior ministers from both sides of the Channel expected to take part.

Mr Cameron and Mr Hollande will also eat lunch together, but without their other halves.

‘I do not think there is a spouses' programme, no,’ Mr Cameron's official spokesman told reporters.

